"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "2376: kingdom of God, coming of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2376",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The kingdom of God comes into being wherever the kingly authority of God is acknowledged. Although God is always sovereign, Scripture looks to a future “realm” or “reign” of salvation. This has come in Christ and yet will come in its fulness only when Jesus Christ returns.</p>\n<h2>God is sovereign over Israel and over the whole earth</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:7-Ps47:8\">PSA 47:7–47:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:18\">EXO 15:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam12:12\">1SA 12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:31\">1CH 16:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:5\">1CH 28:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:11-1Chr29:12\">1CH 29:11–29:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:7-Ps9:8\">PSA 9:7–9:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:6\">PSA 45:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps93:1-Ps93:2\">PSA 93:1–93:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:19\">PSA 103:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:11-Ps145:13\">PSA 145:11–145:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:16\">ISA 37:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:34-Dan4:35\">DAN 4:34–4:35</a></p>\n<h2>The coming reign of God</h2>\n<h3>Its expectation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:4-Isa51:5\">ISA 51:4–51:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:43\">MRK 15:43</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:51\">LUK 23:51</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:2-Isa2:4\">ISA 2:2–2:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:1-Mic4:3\">MIC 4:1–4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:1\">ISA 32:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:17\">JER 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:44\">DAN 2:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:18\">DAN 7:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:21-Dan7:22\">DAN 7:21–7:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:27\">DAN 7:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:22\">ZEC 8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:9\">ZEC 14:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:10\">MRK 11:10</a></p>\n<h3>Its assocication with the coming of the Messiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6-Isa9:7\">ISA 9:6–9:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:14\">DAN 7:14</a></strong> <em>“Son of Man” was Jesus Christ's usual way of referring to himself.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1-Isa11:9\">ISA 11:1–11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5-Jer23:6\">JER 23:5–23:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:2\">MIC 5:2</a></p>\n<h2>The kingdom of God was central in the preaching of Jesus Christ and the apostles</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:14\">MAT 24:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:1\">LUK 8:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:31\">ACT 28:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:17\">MAT 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:23\">MAT 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:35\">MAT 9:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:7\">MAT 10:7</a> <em>Jesus Christ's instructions to the Twelve</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:13-Mark1:14\">MRK 1:13–1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:43\">LUK 4:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:2\">LUK 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:11\">LUK 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:9\">LUK 10:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:3\">ACT 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:6-Acts1:8\">ACT 1:6–1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:12\">ACT 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts19:8\">ACT 19:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:25\">ACT 20:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:23\">ACT 28:23</a></p>\n<h2>The kingdom of God has come in Christ: it is present</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:12\">MAT 11:12</a></strong> <em>Following the Jewish convention of avoiding the use of the divine name, Matthew usually speaks of “the kingdom of heaven”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:1-Matt3:2\">MAT 3:1–3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:17\">MAT 4:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:31-Matt13:32\">MAT 13:31–13:32</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:30-Mark4:32\">MRK 4:30–4:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:18-Luke13:19\">LUK 13:18–13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:33\">MAT 13:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:20-Luke13:21\">LUK 13:20–13:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:28\">MAT 16:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:1\">MRK 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:27\">LUK 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:20\">LUK 11:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:16\">LUK 16:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:20-Luke17:21\">LUK 17:20–17:21</a></p>\n<h2>The kingdom of God will come in its fulness only when Jesus Christ returns: it is future</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:18\">LUK 22:18</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:29\">MAT 26:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:25\">MRK 14:25</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:10\">MAT 6:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:2\">LUK 11:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31\">MAT 25:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:34\">MAT 25:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:16\">LUK 22:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:24\">1CO 15:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:18\">2TI 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:15\">REV 11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:10\">REV 12:10</a></p>",
